The paper deals with robust estimation in high dimensions, which is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes algorithms for robust estimation that have state-of-the-art performance. The second most likely category is cs.STAT (Statistics), as the paper deals with sample complexity bounds and distributional models. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes algorithms with improved time and sample complexity. The fourth likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with the problem of robust estimation in the presence of corruptions. The fifth likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as the paper proposes algorithms for solving optimization problems.
